A senior NHS children’s brain doctor exposed as a cocaine user by The Mail on Sunday has been arrested on suspicion of being involved in the supply of Class A drugs.

Inquiries into paediatric neurologist Dr Colin Ferrie began last month after the MoS printed photos taken from a video appearing to show Ferrie snorting cocaine and swallowing the ‘date rape’ drug GHB, just before going on call.

On Wednesday morning, the consultant was arrested at his home near Bradford and taken to Leeds police headquarters for questioning.

